The paper discusses the optimization and generalization properties of two-layer neural network models, which are commonly used in machine learning and fall under the category of deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of gradient descent dynamics, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category. The paper also compares the neural network models with kernel methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of random feature models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
